     1	# Phase 0 Proof Runbook
     2	
     3	## Purpose
     4	
     5	Run and verify a reproducible Phase 0 proof pack that maps every BDD scenario
     6	(`1.1` through `8.1`) to both positive and falsification evidence.
     7	
     8	Canonical BDD source: `docs/rewrite/PHASE0_PROOF_BDD.md`.
     9	
    10	---
    11	
    12	## Prerequisites
    13	
    14	- Repo is checked out at the desired commit.
    15	- Rust toolchain and `cargo-nextest` are installed (same requirements as `just ci`).
    16	- `tanren-cli` and `tanren-mcp` are installed and PATH-callable.
    17	- Python runtime is available through `uv` (for proof helper scripts).
    18	- `jq` is installed and PATH-callable.
    19	
    20	Recommended bootstrap from repo root:
    21	
    22	```bash
    23	uv sync
    24	scripts/runtime/install-runtime.sh
    25	scripts/runtime/verify-installed-runtime.sh
    26	```
    27	
    28	---
    29	
    30	## Hard Cutover Status
    31	
    32	The legacy one-command proof collector (`scripts/proof/phase0/run.sh`) is
    33	retired during Rust testing hard cutover.
    34	
    35	Current behavior-proof commands are:
    36	
    37	```bash
    38	just check-phase0-bdd-smoke
    39	just check-phase0-bdd-wave-a
    40	just check-phase0-mutation-stage
    41	just check-phase0-stage-gates
    42	```
    43	
    44	Policy and allowed post-cutover forms:
    45	
    46	- `docs/rewrite/PHASE0_RUST_TEST_CUTOVER_POLICY.md`
    47	
    48	---
    49	
    50	## Verification
    51	
    52	Run explicit verification against an existing pack generated before cutover:
    53	
    54	```bash
    55	scripts/proof/phase0/verify.sh artifacts/phase0-proof/<timestamp>
    56	```
    57	
    58	`verify.sh` fails non-zero when any of these are missing or invalid:
    59	
    60	- `summary.json` / `summary.md`
    61	- `runtime/installed-runtime.json` with `runtime_ok=true`
    62	- positive/falsification `PASS` markers for every scenario `1.1` through `8.1`
    63	- auth/replay supplemental reports
    64	- replay parity + rollback verdicts
    65	- manual walkthrough summary
    66	
    67	---
    68	
    69	## Phase 0 Orchestration Entry Point
    70	
    71	Phase 0 now ships a reusable, non-Python orchestration entrypoint:
    72	
    73	```bash
    74	scripts/orchestration/phase0.sh --spec-id <spec-uuid> --spec-folder <spec-folder>
    75	```
    76	
    77	Behavior contract:
    78	
    79	- Resumes from store truth via `tanren-cli methodology spec status`.
    80	- Autonomous loop runs Phase 0 task/spec gates and agentic phases through
    81	  Codex harness invocation (`codex exec`) only.
    82	- Harness override mode is intentionally disabled in acceptance flow
    83	  (`--harness-cmd` and `TANREN_PHASE0_HARNESS_CMD` are rejected).
    84	- Breaks out only at required human checkpoints:
    85	  - missing spec -> prompt `shape-spec`
    86	  - blocker halt -> prompt `resolve-blockers`
    87	  - walk-ready -> prompt `walk-spec`
    88	- Uses hook commands resolved from `tanren.yml` (task/spec/per-phase hooks)
    89	  and records resolved config in run artifacts under:
    90	  `<spec-folder>/orchestration/phase0/<timestamp>/`.
    91	- Supports output modes via `--output-mode` (or `TANREN_PHASE0_OUTPUT_MODE`):
    92	  - `silent` (default): single-line high-level progress (`task N/M - <verb>`).
    93	  - `quiet`: task definition + deliverable summary + high-level action/result.
    94	  - `verbose`: full command/harness logging.
    95	
    96	Recommended operator flow:
    97	
    98	1. Manually shape the spec (`shape-spec`).
    99	2. Run `scripts/orchestration/phase0.sh ...`.
   100	3. When prompted for walk readiness, manually run `walk-spec`.
   101	
   102	---
   103	
   104	## Staged Gate Scaffolding (Current Non-Blocking Contract)
   105	
   106	While the Rust testing cutover is in progress, staged gate scaffolds are
   107	available in `justfile` and exercised by CI:
   108	
   109	```bash
   110	just check-phase0-scenario-stage
   111	just check-phase0-bdd-smoke
   112	just check-phase0-bdd-wave-a
   113	just check-phase0-mutation-stage
   114	just check-phase0-coverage-stage
   115	just check-phase0-stage-gates
   116	```
   117	
   118	Current behavior:
   119	
   120	- commands are non-blocking scaffolds that emit readiness/status signals,
   121	- `check-phase0-bdd-smoke` executes a cucumber-rs smoke scenario and emits the
   122	  feature tag line as traceability evidence,
   123	- `check-phase0-bdd-wave-a` executes Wave A feature files (`1.1` through `3.2`)
   124	  and emits BEH-tag evidence for each file,
   125	- `check-phase0-mutation-stage` executes a sampled `cargo-mutants` run (when
   126	  installed) and writes machine-readable survivor triage to
   127	  `artifacts/phase0-mutation/staged/latest/triage.json`,
   128	- they are intended for per-task demonstrability while implementation lands,
   129	- strict blocking enforcement remains a later cutover task.
   130	
   131	---
   132	
   133	## Artifact Layout
   134	
   135	```text
   136	artifacts/phase0-proof/<timestamp>/
   137	  summary.json
   138	  summary.md
   139	  scenarios/
   140	    <scenario-id>/
   141	      positive/
   142	      falsification/
   143	  auth-replay/
   144	    summary.json
   145	  replay-pack/
   146	    source-event-stream.jsonl
   147	    target-task-list.json
   148	    verdicts/
   149	      equivalence.json
   150	      rollback.json
   151	  manual-walkthrough/
   152	    phase-events.jsonl
   153	    summary.json
   154	    steps/
   155	```
   156	
   157	---
   158	
   159	## Reading Results
   160	
   161	1. Open `summary.md` for a human-readable matrix.
   162	2. Open `summary.json` for machine-readable status.
   163	3. For any failing scenario, inspect:
   164	   - `scenarios/<id>/<kind>/command.txt`
   165	   - `scenarios/<id>/<kind>/stdout.log`
   166	   - `scenarios/<id>/<kind>/stderr.log`
   167	
   168	Replay-specific interpretation:
   169	
   170	- `replay-pack/verdicts/equivalence.json`: source vs replayed state parity.
   171	- `replay-pack/verdicts/rollback.json`: invalid replay rejection and no-partial-apply guarantee.
   172	
   173	---
   174	
   175	## Token Troubleshooting
   176	
   177	Token helper:
   178	
   179	```bash
   180	uv run python scripts/proof/phase0/mint_actor_token.py \
   181	  --private-key-pem <path> \
   182	  --issuer tanren-phase0-proof \
   183	  --audience tanren-cli \
   184	  --org-id 00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000000a1 \
   185	  --user-id 00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000000b1 \
   186	  --mode valid \
   187	  --requested-ttl 600 \
   188	  --max-ttl 900 \
   189	  --token-only
   190	```
   191	
   192	The utility always prints computed token math to stderr:
   193	
   194	- `iat`
   195	- `exp`
   196	- `exp_minus_iat`
   197	- configured `max_ttl`
   198	
   199	Invariant enforced:
   200	
   201	- non-`ttl_over_max` modes fail when `exp_minus_iat > actor_token_max_ttl_secs`
   202	
   203	Operational rule:
   204	
   205	- derive `exp` from `iat` (`exp = iat + requested_ttl`), not from independent wall-clock math.
   206	
   207	---
   208	
   209	## CI + Ship Gate
   210	
   211	After proof pack generation and verification:
   212	
   213	```bash
   214	just ci
   215	lefthook run pre-commit
   216	```
   217	
   218	Then stage/commit/push with a clean `git status`.

